OL,6,FBoth trains involved in the crash were
OL,7,Ftwo-carriage class 158 units.
OL,9,FThe train with the failed sanding
OL,10,Fsystem was travelling west to
OL,11,FAberystwyth.
OL,13,FIt was supposed to stop inside a loop
OL,14,Fto allow an eastbound train to pass on
OL,15,Fthe single track section of the
OL,16,FCambrian line.
OL,18,FAnalysis of the on-board data recorder
OL,19,Fshows the driver applied the brakes as
OL,20,Fthe train neared the loop, during
OL,21,Fwhich time the wheels began to slide.
